cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

The paper addresses the problem of constructing a knowledge base of entity-oriented search intents, which involves natural language processing, information retrieval, and machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves data management and organization, which suggests cs.DB (Databases) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the evaluation of performance and quality of data suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a potential sub-category.
